Azure DNS is a hosting service for DNS domains that provides name resolution using Microsoft Azure infrastructure.

It translates human-readable domain names into IP addresses.

For example, [www.example.com](http://www.example.com) is resolved to an IP address where the website is hosted.

A real-life use case is hosting domain records for applications deployed in Azure.

Another example is managing DNS zones for global services.

Azure DNS ensures reliable and scalable domain resolution.
